## **Solution Options:**

**Option 1: Configure Tailwind to use `data-theme` (Recommended)**
Add custom variant to global.css to make Tailwind's `dark:` prefix work with `[data-theme="dark"]`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@custom-variant dark (&:where([data-theme="dark"], [data-theme="dark"] *));
```

**Option 2: Use system `prefers-color-scheme` everywhere**
Remove the `[data-theme="dark"]` selectors and use `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` instead.

Which approach would you prefer? Option 1 gives you manual toggle control, Option 2 respects system preferences automatically.

